%EndExpansion
(10ed-10.1-11) Calculate $\int_{C}\mathbf{F}\cdot d\mathbf{r}$ for $\mathbf{%
F=}\left[ e^{-x},e^{-y},e^{-z}\right] $ and $\mathbf{r=}\left[ t,t^{2},t%
\right] $ from $\left( 0,0,0\right) $ to $\left( 2,4,2\right) .$ Show the
details.

%TCIMACRO{\TeXButton{blue}{\color[rgb]{0,0,1}}}%
%BeginExpansion
\color[rgb]{0,0,1}%
%EndExpansion
\textbf{Solution:} 
%TCIMACRO{\TeXButton{blueEnd}{\color[rgb]{0,0,0}}}%
%BeginExpansion
\color[rgb]{0,0,0}%
%EndExpansion
Initial and terminal points indicate variation of $t$ as $0\leq t\leq 2.$
Next rewriting $\mathbf{F}$ in terms of $t$ only, by using $x=t,y=t^{2}$ and 
$z=t\Rightarrow \mathbf{F=}\left[ e^{-t},e^{-t^{2}},e^{-t}\right] .$ Hence%
\begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{C}\mathbf{F}\cdot d\mathbf{r} &\mathbf{=}&\int_{0}^{2}\left( \left[
e^{-t},e^{-t^{2}},e^{-t}\right] \cdot \frac{d}{dt}\left[ t,t^{2},t\right]
\right) dt \\
&=&\int_{0}^{2}\left( \left[ e^{-t},e^{-t^{2}},e^{-t}\right] \cdot \left[
1,2t,1\right] \right) dt \\
&=&\int_{0}^{2}\left( 2e^{-t}+2te^{-t^{2}}\right) dt \\
&=&\allowbreak 3-\frac{2}{e^{2}}-\frac{1}{e^{4}}
\end{eqnarray*}%
