(10ed-10.1-15) Without taking dot product, evaluate the line integral with $%
\mathbf{F=}\left[ y^{2},z^{2},x^{2}\right] $ and $C:\left[ 3\cos t,3\sin t,2t%
\right] ;~0\leq t\leq 4\pi ?$

%TCIMACRO{\TeXButton{blue}{\color[rgb]{0,0,1}}}%
%BeginExpansion
\color[rgb]{0,0,1}%
%EndExpansion
\textbf{Solution:} 
%TCIMACRO{\TeXButton{blueEnd}{\color[rgb]{0,0,0}}}%
%BeginExpansion
\color[rgb]{0,0,0}%
%EndExpansion
From the curve we have $x=3\cos t,y=3\sin t$ and $z=2t.$ By using the form 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{C}\mathbf{F}\left( \mathbf{r}\right) dt &=&\int_{a}^{b}\mathbf{F}%
\left( \mathbf{r}\left( t\right) \right) dt=\int_{a}^{b}\left[ \mathbf{F}%
_{1}\left( \mathbf{r}\left( t\right) \right) ,~\mathbf{F}_{2}\left( \mathbf{r%
}\left( t\right) \right) ,~\mathbf{F}_{3}\left( \mathbf{r}\left( t\right)
\right) \right] dt \\
&=&\int_{0}^{4\pi }\left[ \left( 3\sin t\right) ^{2},\left( 2t\right)
^{2},\left( 3\cos t\right) ^{2}\right] dt \\
&=&\left[ \int_{0}^{4\pi }\left( 3\sin t\right) ^{2}dt,~\int_{0}^{4\pi
}\left( 2t\right) ^{2}dt,~\int_{0}^{4\pi }\left( 3\cos t\right) ^{2}dt\right]
\\
&=&\allowbreak \left[ 18\pi ,\frac{256}{3}\pi ^{3},18\pi \right]
~~~~~\blacksquare
\end{eqnarray*}

